The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 16 March is 40,916 (4,735.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 11 March, there were 290 new confirmed cases (33.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 04 March, there were 336 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 14% (46 fewer cases).
